  "title": "Applications Become Data",
  "description": "Part 4 of a 6-part series on AI-native computing. A schema, its records, and a model make a complete application — the AI authors all three layers, per user. Companion video to the essay of the same name.",
  "lang": "en",
  "beats": [
    {
      "text": "Applications become data. This is part four of a six part series. Part one said the future rests on two pillars — the computer that understands, and the computer that builds. This time we follow the second pillar all the way down. What is an application, once a machine can build one?",
      "image": {
        "type": "slide",
        "slide": {
          "layout": "title",
          "eyebrow": {
            "label": "Part 4 of 6 · Beyond the Sea of App Icons"
          },
          "titleSize": "hero",
          "subtitleSize": "lead",
          "title": "Applications **Become Data**",
          "subtitle": "Following {accent:the computer that builds} all the way down",
          "author": "Satoshi Nakajima",
          "chips": [
            "🗣️ the computer that understands",
            "🛠️ the computer that builds"
          ]
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "text": "Remember Maria, the soap maker? Good news: a dozen shops now stock her soap. Bad news: the invoices have outgrown a folder of PDFs. So she says to her computer — track the invoices I send my wholesale accounts. Who has paid, who is late. A moment later, there is an invoice tracker. Overdue rows flagged. The total she is owed at the top. And it's correct.",
      "image": {
        "type": "html_tailwind",
        "html": "<div class=\"w-[1280px] h-[720px] overflow-hidden flex flex-col\" style=\"background: radial-gradient(1200px 700px at 12% -10%, rgba(56,189,248,.16), transparent 60%), radial-gradient(1000px 600px at 100% 0%, rgba(129,140,248,.16), transparent 55%), linear-gradient(160deg,#0A0F24,#111A3A 55%,#16224D); color:#EEF2FF; font-family:Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif\"><div class=\"pt-11 text-center\"><span class=\"text-[13px] font-semibold uppercase\" style=\"letter-spacing:.35em;color:#38BDF8\">An application from a sentence</span></div><div class=\"flex-1 flex items-center justify-center gap-5 px-10\"><div class=\"bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-2xl p-6 w-[320px]\"><div class=\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\"><span class=\"text-2xl\">🧼</span><span class=\"text-[13px] font-semibold\" style=\"color:#9FB0D8\">Maria says</span></div><div class=\"rounded-2xl rounded-bl-sm p-4 text-[17px] leading-snug\" style=\"background:rgba(56,189,248,.14);border:1px solid rgba(56,189,248,.35)\">“Track my wholesale invoices — who owes me what, and when it&#39;s due.”</div></div><div class=\"text-4xl\" style=\"color:#38BDF8;text-shadow:0 0 18px rgba(56,189,248,.8)\">→</div><div class=\"bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-2xl p-5 w-[300px] font-mono text-[14px] leading-relaxed\"><div class=\"flex items-center justify-between mb-3\"><span style=\"color:#9FB0D8\">schema.json</span><span class=\"text-[12px] px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full\" style=\"color:#34D399;background:rgba(52,211,153,.12);border:1px solid rgba(52,211,153,.4)\">✓ valid</span></div><div style=\"color:#6F7FA0\">{</div><div class=\"pl-5\"><span style=\"color:#38BDF8\">&quot;client&quot;</span>: &quot;ref&quot;,</div><div class=\"pl-5\"><span style=\"color:#38BDF8\">&quot;amount&quot;</span>: &quot;money&quot;,</div><div class=\"pl-5\"><span style=\"color:#38BDF8\">&quot;dueOn&quot;</span>: &quot;date&quot;,</div><div class=\"pl-5\"><span style=\"color:#38BDF8\">&quot;status&quot;</span>: &quot;draft|sent|paid&quot;</div><div style=\"color:#6F7FA0\">}</div></div><div class=\"text-4xl\" style=\"color:#818CF8;text-shadow:0 0 18px rgba(129,140,248,.8)\">→</div><div class=\"bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-2xl p-5 w-[360px]\"><div class=\"flex items-baseline justify-between mb-3\"><span class=\"text-[16px] font-semibold\">Invoices</span><span class=\"text-[13px]\" style=\"color:#9FB0D8\">owed: <span class=\"font-mono\" style=\"color:#EEF2FF\">$2,965</span></span></div><div class=\"flex items-center justify-between rounded-xl px-3 py-2 mb-2 text-[13px]\" style=\"background:rgba(255,255,255,.04);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.08)\"><span>Harbor Goods</span><span class=\"font-mono text-[12px]\" style=\"color:#9FB0D8\">$1,240 · Jul 15</span><span class=\"text-[11px] px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full\" style=\"color:#34D399;background:rgba(52,211,153,.12);border:1px solid rgba(52,211,153,.4)\">paid</span></div><div class=\"flex items-center justify-between rounded-xl px-3 py-2 mb-2 text-[13px]\" style=\"background:rgba(255,255,255,.04);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.08)\"><span>Cedar &amp; Co</span><span class=\"font-mono text-[12px]\" style=\"color:#9FB0D8\">$860 · Jul 22</span><span class=\"text-[11px] px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full\" style=\"color:#38BDF8;background:rgba(56,189,248,.12);border:1px solid rgba(56,189,248,.4)\">sent</span></div><div class=\"flex items-center justify-between rounded-xl px-3 py-2 text-[13px]\" style=\"background:rgba(251,191,36,.06);border:1px solid rgba(251,191,36,.3)\"><span>Bluebird Market</span><span class=\"font-mono text-[12px]\" style=\"color:#9FB0D8\">$2,105 · Jul 1</span><span class=\"text-[11px] px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full\" style=\"color:#FBBF24;background:rgba(251,191,36,.12);border:1px solid rgba(251,191,36,.4)\">overdue</span></div></div></div><div class=\"pb-11 text-center text-[16px]\" style=\"color:#9FB0D8\">No database server. No deployment. No vendor.</div></div>"
      }
    },
    {
      "text": "Now look at what did not happen. She didn't pick a vendor. Nothing was installed. No database server, no deployment. And the strange part — nobody wrote this app for her in advance. What appeared on her disk was a small schema file, and a folder of records. The third ingredient isn't on disk at all. It's the model that reads both.",
      "image": {
        "type": "slide",
        "slide": {
          "layout": "split",
          "eyebrow": {
            "label": "What just happened"
          },
          "left": {
            "title": "What didn't happen",
            "accentColor": "warning",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "bullets",
                "items": [
                  "No vendor, no subscription",
                  "No server, no deployment",
                  "No code written in advance"
                ]
              }
            ],
            "ratio": 50
          },
          "right": {
            "title": "What appeared",
            "accentColor": "primary",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "bullets",
                "items": [
                  "A schema — a few lines of JSON",
                  "Records — one file per invoice",
                  "A model that reads both"
                ]
              }
            ],
            "ratio": 50
          }
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "text": "A traditional application is four separate systems. A database to hold the records. An O R M to translate them. A U I framework to put them on screen. And a workflow engine to make things happen. In Maria's tracker, the database became plain files. The O R M simply vanished. The U I is rendered from the schema itself. And the workflow split between strict host rules and plain prose.",
      "image": {
        "type": "slide",
        "slide": {
          "layout": "grid",
          "eyebrow": {
            "label": "The collapse"
          },
          "title": "Four systems become one schema",
          "gridColumns": 2,
          "items": [
            {
              "title": "Database",
              "description": "became plain files you own",
              "icon": "🗄️"
            },
            {
              "title": "ORM",
              "description": "simply vanished",
              "icon": "🔁"
            },
            {
              "title": "UI framework",
              "description": "views rendered from the schema",
              "icon": "🖼️"
            },
            {
              "title": "Workflow engine",
              "description": "strict host rules + plain prose",
              "icon": "⚙️"
            }
          ],
          "footer": "All four, collapsed into one artifact: the schema."
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "text": "So here is the whole application, written as an equation. A schema — the fields, the rules, the formulas. The records it describes. And a model that reads them. That's it. That's the entire stack. It's a spreadsheet's old bargain — columns, rows, a recalculating engine — except this runtime reasons.",
      "image": {
        "type": "slide",
        "slide": {
          "layout": "columns",
          "eyebrow": {
            "label": "The equation"
          },
          "title": "schema + records + model",
          "columns": [
            {
              "title": "Schema",
              "accentColor": "primary",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": "**The fields, the rules, the formulas.**"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": "A few dozen lines of JSON",
                  "dim": true
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "title": "Records",
              "accentColor": "info",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": "**One small file per invoice.**"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
